olive oil
3 clove garlic
1 bag parsley
1 bag mint
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 packet chicken thigh
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
½ sachet dried oregano
¾ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 tsp honey
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 drizzle red wine vinegar
1 packet haloumi/grill cheese
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
6 Mini Flour Tortillas

• Preheat BBQ to medium-high heat. Finely chop
garlic, parsley and mint leaves. Roughly chop
tomato and cucumber.
• Pat haloumi dry with paper towel and cut into
1cm slices. Place haloumi on a plate, drizzle
with olive oil and toss to coat.
• In a small bowl, combine mint, Greek-style
yoghurt and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with
salt and set aside.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken thigh,
garlic & herb seasoning, dried oregano (see
ingredients), a generous drizzle of olive oil and
1/2 the garlic. Season with pepper and set aside.

• In a medium saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook remaining garlic
until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the water and chicken-style stock powder
and bring to the boil. Add couscous and stir
to combine.
• Cover with a lid and remove from heat. Set aside
until all the water is absorbed, 5 minutes.
Fluff up with a fork, then stir through parsley.

• When the BBQ is hot, add chicken to BBQ grill
plate and cook, turning occasionally, until
charred and cooked through, 8-12 minutes.
Transfer to a plate.

NO BBQ? In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive
oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken, turning
occasionally, until browned and cooked through,
14-16 minutes.

• Add haloumi to the BBQ flat plate and grill until
golden brown, 2-3 minutes each side. Transfer
haloumi to a plate and drizzle over the honey.

TIP: Avoid using the grill plate to cook your haloumi
in case it gets stuck!

No BBQ or flat plate? In a large frying pan, heat
a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook
haloumi until golden brown, 2 minutes each side.
Remove pan from heat and add the honey, turning
haloumi to coat.

• Brush mini flour tortillas with olive oil. Grill
tortillas on BBQ flat plate until golden and
warmed through, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Meanwhile, in a second medium bowl, combine
cucumber, tomato, mixed salad leaves and a
drizzle of red wine vinegar and olive oil. Season
with salt and pepper.

No BBQ or flat plate? Brush or spread some olive
oil over both sides of a mini flour tortilla. Heat a
large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast
tortilla until golden, 1 minute each side. Transfer to
a paper towel-lined plate. Repeat with remaining
tortillas and olive oil.

• Toss garden salad. Slice grilled chicken. Bring
everything to the table to serve.
• Help yourself to chargrilled Greek-style chicken,
garlic couscous, honey haloumi, garden salad,
tortillas and mint yoghurt. Enjoy!